<Layout
  title="About Jackie B III — Going Loopy"
  description="About Jackie B III, the crew, and the Great Loop voyage from 2022 to 2024."
>
  <div class="max-w-[720px] mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="font-inter font-bold text-[28px] text-ink leading-[1.2] mb-8">About Jackie B III</h1>

    <div class="font-lora text-[18px] text-ink leading-[1.7]">
      <p class="mb-6">
        Jackie B III is a powerboat that completed the Great Loop — a 5,424-nautical-mile continuous waterway
        circuit through the eastern United States, Canada, and the Gulf of Mexico — from April 2022 through
        May 2024. This site is the permanent record of that voyage, documented stop by stop along the way.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6">
        The Great Loop follows a connected system of rivers, lakes, canals, and coastal waterways: up the
        Atlantic Intracoastal Waterway, through the Great Lakes, down the Mississippi and Tennessee-Tombigbee
        waterways, across the Gulf of Mexico, around Florida, and back up the East Coast to the starting point
        in New Bern, NC. Every anchorage, every marina, every town along the way is documented here.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6">
        This site was built to share the voyage with family and friends who followed along, and with the
        broader Great Loop community. The trip is complete — but the stories are still being published.
        Stub content only — full About page coming in a later phase.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
